<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11105i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11105i">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11105i"> 105(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Dysmas Gestas <font face="wake">+</font> <font face="wake">+</font> <font face="wake">+</font></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Dysmas is crucified on the right hand <font color="green">[116]</font> and Gestas on the left. 103: Then Pilate commanded the veil to be drawn before the judgement-seat whereon he sat, and saith unto Jesus: Thy nation hath convicted thee (accused thee) as <i>being</i> a king: therefore have I decreed that thou shouldest first be scourged according to the law of the pious emperors, and thereafter hanged upon the cross in the garden wherein thou wast taken: and let <mark>Dysmas and Gestas the two malefactors be crucified with thee</mark>. <small> James, M. R, ed., <a name="APOC" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#APOC"><cite title="source">The Apocryphal New Testament</cite></a> (1924) 116-17</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
